{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777742291800,"sessionID":"ses_21652b159ffetKEIjuAlMIK8KR","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_00_wyijLBVJQDsDT4afIyVH7863","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs-pilot/deepseek-v4-pro-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-001-r1s0.yaml","content":"id: hyp-20260502-001-r1s0\ntitle: \"Eliminate load-use stall via MEM-stage forwarding\"\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The current 5-stage pipeline inserts 1 bubble cycle on every load-use\n  pair — when a LOAD in EX/MEM is immediately followed by a dependent\n  instruction in ID/EX. The hazard_unit forces stall_if / flush_id and\n  the dependent instruction waits until the LOAD reaches WB before it can\n  enter EX. CoreMark has a meaningful fraction of load-use pairs (~5–10%\n  of dynamic instructions), so eliminating this stall yields a direct IPC\n  gain. The dmem_rdata is available combinationally during the MEM stage,\n  so this is a classic textbook forwarding optimization (P&H §4.7).\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a third forwarding source to the EX-stage operand muxes: the\n  sign/zero-extended load data from the MEM stage's combinational\n  dmem_rdata path. When the forward_unit detects that the instruction\n  in MEM (EX/MEM register) is a write-enabled LOAD whose destination\n  matches the EX-stage's source register, it selects the MEM-stage load\n  data (priority: MEM load > EX/MEM ALU > MEM/WB > none). The hazard_unit\n  then drops the load-use stall because forwarding now covers the\n  dependency. The dependent instruction enters EX one cycle earlier and\n  the pipeline sustains single-cycle throughput through load-use pairs.\n  Fmax impact from the longer combinational path (dmem_rdata → byte-extract\n  → forward-mux → ALU) is expected to be small on FPGA BRAM (~1–2 LUT\n  levels added to the existing ALU path).\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n    description: |\n      Add ex_mem_is_load and ex_mem_mem_read (ctrl.mem_read) inputs.\n      When ex_mem_is_load && ex_mem_w_en && ex_mem_rd != 0 && ex_mem_rd == rs,\n      output fwd=2'd3 (MEM-stage load data) instead of 2'd1.\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: |\n      Add input ports: fwd_dmem_rdata [31:0], fwd_mem_width [1:0],\n      fwd_mem_sext, fwd_mem_addr [1:0]. Compute sign/zero-extended load\n      value from these. Add case 2'd3 to the fwd_rs* muxes selecting\n      this computed load data.\n  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n    description: |\n      Remove load_use_hazard logic and its contributions to stall_if,\n      stall_id, and flush_id — the forwarding path now covers this case.\n      Keep the dmem_stall and redirect/imem_stall paths intact.\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: |\n      Wire io_dmemRData to ex_stage.fwd_dmem_rdata. Wire\n      ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_width, ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_sext, and\n      ex_mem_w.alu_result[1:0] to the new ex_stage inputs. Wire\n      ex_mem_w.ctrl.mem_read to forward_unit.ex_mem_is_load.\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs-pilot/deepseek-v4-pro-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-001-r1s0.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-001-r1s0.yaml","time":{"start":1777742291793,"end":1777742291799}},"id":"prt_de9b24091001DZH0pacAF1p5vY","sessionID":"ses_21652b159ffetKEIjuAlMIK8KR","messageID":"msg_de9b0576b001TpEf1PKrJZoAt4"}}
