{"type":"text","timestamp":1777742239676,"sessionID":"ses_21652b0c1ffe6Y7fjGIeXb8ulr","part":{"id":"prt_de9b1c5f4001ElJRY8TcFYVyzZ","messageID":"msg_de9b1a1d6001pZXlgyQIf2AycN","sessionID":"ses_21652b0c1ffe6Y7fjGIeXb8ulr","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis written to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-002-r1s1.yaml`. \n\nThe proposal adds a 16-entry direct-mapped BTB to eliminate the 2-cycle taken-branch penalty on correctly predicted branches. CoreMark's tight loops make backward branches highly predictable, so the expected CPI improvement is ~0.12, yielding a ~10% fitness gain. The BTB is a small structural addition (~200 LUTs) that fits within the headroom (120 LUTs remaining out of 10,000) and reuses the existing redirect/flush mechanism for misprediction recovery.","time":{"start":1777742235124,"end":1777742239673}}}
