{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777742334854,"sessionID":"ses_21652b059ffezeCHMDlF3WVOZk","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_00_BtpYDJiz4PLdsBNrJMct3718","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs-pilot/deepseek-v4-pro-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-003-r1s2.yaml","content":"id: hyp-20260502-003-r1s2\ntitle: \"Bimodal BHT with ID-stage branch redirect\"\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  The baseline 5-stage pipeline resolves all branches in EX with a 2-cycle\n  taken-penalty (IF+ID flush). JAL/JALR also pay the same penalty despite\n  JAL being unconditional. Adding a small bimodal branch history table that\n  predicts branch direction in the ID stage reduces the taken-branch penalty\n  to 0 cycles for correctly-predicted branches, increasing IPC significantly\n  for CoreMark's loop-heavy workload at minimal hardware cost.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a 64-entry 2-bit saturating-counter bimodal BHT indexed by PC[7:2].\n  The BHT is read combinationally in the ID stage in parallel with decode.\n  When the prediction is \"taken\" (counter MSB=1) or the instruction is JAL,\n  the ID stage computes the target (PC+imm, already available from imm_gen)\n  and asserts a predict_redirect signal back to the IF stage, causing the PC\n  to jump to the target on the next clock edge. The predicted direction is\n  stored in the ID/EX register. In EX, the actual branch outcome is compared\n  against the prediction; on mispredict, the EX stage flushes IF+ID and\n  redirects to the correct target (same mechanism as current EX redirect).\n  JAL is always predicted taken unconditionally. JALR continues to resolve\n  in EX. The BHT is updated synchronously from EX with the actual branch\n  outcome using saturating up/down counters. This should increase IPC by\n  ~15-25% for CoreMark, with a modest LUT cost (~128 FFs for the BHT, plus\n  prediction/mispredict logic).\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 12\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/bht.sv\n    description: \"New module: 64-entry 2-bit saturating-counter bimodal BHT. Combinational read port for ID stage, synchronous update port driven by EX branch resolution.\"\n  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n    description: \"Integrate BHT lookup. On predicted-taken (or JAL), assert predict_redirect and compute redirect target = PC+imm. Pass predicted_taken flag through ID/EX for EX-stage verification.\"\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: \"Accept predict_redirect and predict_target from ID stage as a second redirect source (lower priority than EX redirect). Redirect PC when predict_redirect is asserted.\"\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: \"Compare predicted direction (from ID/EX predicted_taken field) with actual branch resolution. On mispredict, assert mispredict_redirect to flush IF+ID and correct PC. Generate BHT update signals (update_valid, update_index, update_taken).\"\n  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n    description: \"Accept mispredict_redirect input; treat identically to current EX redirect (assert flush_if and flush_id to kill wrong-path instructions following a mispredicted branch).\"\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: \"Wire predict_redirect and predict_target from ID to IF; wire mispredict_redirect from EX to hazard_unit; instantiate bht module and connect read/update ports between ID, EX, and BHT.\"\n  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n    description: \"Add predicted_taken bit to id_ex_t struct so EX stage can compare prediction against actual branch outcome.\"\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs-pilot/deepseek-v4-pro-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-003-r1s2.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-003-r1s2.yaml","time":{"start":1777742334847,"end":1777742334854}},"id":"prt_de9b2e30a0010Q6NRAjR4e05Co","sessionID":"ses_21652b059ffezeCHMDlF3WVOZk","messageID":"msg_de9b0f9070016YDmJErWpKNXba"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1777742335284,"sessionID":"ses_21652b059ffezeCHMDlF3WVOZk","part":{"id":"prt_de9b2d636001CUG66p51ybRkrI","messageID":"msg_de9b0f9070016YDmJErWpKNXba","sessionID":"ses_21652b059ffezeCHMDlF3WVOZk","type":"text","text":"Now I have a clear picture. No prior hypotheses exist (the other agents logged exploration but never wrote YAML files), and no LESSONS.md exists. The baseline is a 5-stage in-order core with no branch prediction — all taken branches pay a 2-cycle penalty.\n\nThe most promising predictor angle: **64-entry bimodal BHT with ID-stage redirect**, reducing correctly-predicted taken-branch penalty from 2 cycles to 0.","time":{"start":1777742304822,"end":1777742335283}}}
