{"type":"text","timestamp":1777742351707,"sessionID":"ses_21652b059ffezeCHMDlF3WVOZk","part":{"id":"prt_de9b37fc5001QNZzEBxTvB3OIp","messageID":"msg_de9b362dd0013Sud6T2eChE6xE","sessionID":"ses_21652b059ffezeCHMDlF3WVOZk","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis written to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260502-003-r1s2.yaml`.\n\n**Summary**: Adds a 64-entry bimodal BHT (2-bit saturating counters, indexed by PC[7:2]) that predicts branch direction in the ID stage. When prediction is \"taken\" (or the instruction is JAL), the ID stage immediately redirects the PC to the target (PC+imm), eliminating the 2-cycle taken-branch penalty for correctly-predicted branches. The EX stage verifies predictions and triggers mispredict recovery. Estimated fitness gain: +12%.","time":{"start":1777742348229,"end":1777742351705}}}
