{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777742692014,"sessionID":"ses_2164e2417ffeuvidBdduDudYvn","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_WXufxo9NZGWVjYycgrdo3149","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs-pilot/deepseek-v4-pro-rep3/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260502-002-r1s1/Makefile"},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs-pilot/deepseek-v4-pro-rep3/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260502-002-r1s1/Makefile</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: .PHONY: help lint test test-infra cosim formal fpga next loop report bench clean\n2: .DEFAULT_GOAL := help\n3: \n4: # Resolve OSS CAD Suite path so commands work even when the user hasn't\n5: # sourced .toolchain/oss-cad-suite/environment in this shell.\n6: TOOLCHAIN_DIR := $(CURDIR)/.toolchain\n7: OSS_BIN       := $(TOOLCHAIN_DIR)/oss-cad-suite/bin\n8: LOCAL_BIN     := $(TOOLCHAIN_DIR)/bin\n9: export PATH := $(OSS_BIN):$(LOCAL_BIN):$(PATH)\n10: \n11: # Orchestrator knobs (pass-through to tools.orchestrator):\n12: #   N        — number of rounds for `make loop` (default 10).\n13: #   K        — tournament size, slots per round (default 1 = sequential).\n14: #   AGENT    — codex (default) or claude. Honors a pre-existing\n15: #              AGENT_PROVIDER env var if AGENT isn't set on the make\n16: #              command line.\n17: #   BASE     — when forking a new TARGET, copy from cores/<BASE>/.\n18: #              Default: baseline (orchestrator-side default).\n19: #   COREMARK — target CoreMark iterations/sec (e.g. '370').\n20: #   LUT      — target LUT count (e.g. '3000').\n21: #   WORKTREE — default ON. `make loop` first creates a dedicated git worktree\n22: #              at .worktrees/<TARGET>/ on branch core-<TARGET> and re-execs\n23: #              itself there. Lets two `make loop` invocations for different\n24: #              TARGETs run in parallel without git index/merge collisions.\n25: #              To opt out (run directly on the current branch + cwd) pass\n26: #              an explicit empty value: `make loop TARGET=v1 WORKTREE=`.\n27: N        ?= 10\n28: K        ?= 1\n29: AGENT    ?= $(or $(AGENT_PROVIDER),codex)\n30: BASE     ?=\n31: COREMARK ?=\n32: LUT      ?=\n33: WORKTREE ?= 1\n34: \n35: # Compose optional CLI flags for the orchestrator. Empty vars produce\n36: # empty strings so the orchestrator falls back to its defaults.\n37: ORCH_FLAGS  = --iterations $(N) --tournament-size $(K)\n38: ifneq ($(strip $(BASE)),)\n39:   ORCH_FLAGS += --base $(BASE)\n40: endif\n41: ifneq ($(strip $(COREMARK)),)\n42:   ORCH_FLAGS += --coremark-target $(COREMARK)\n43: endif\n44: ifneq ($(strip $(LUT)),)\n45:   ORCH_FLAGS += --lut-target $(LUT)\n46: endif\n47: \n48: # Multi-core: TARGET selects the core under cores/<TARGET>/.\n49: # TARGET is required for all core-touching targets (enforced below).\n50: TARGET ?=\n51: \n52: # Targets that require TARGET=<core_name>.\n53: CORE_TARGETS := lint test cosim cosim-build formal formal-deep fpga next loop\n54: \n55: ifeq ($(strip $(TARGET)),)\n56:   ifneq ($(filter $(MAKECMDGOALS),$(CORE_TARGETS)),)\n57:     $(error TARGET= required. Available cores: $(notdir $(wildcard cores/*)))\n58:   endif\n59: endif\n60: \n61: ifneq ($(strip $(TARGET)),)\n62:   RTL_DIR    := cores/$(TARGET)/rtl\n63:   TEST_DIR   := cores/$(TARGET)/test\n64:   CORE_NAME  := $(TARGET)\n65:   OBJ_DIR    := cores/$(TARGET)/obj_dir\n66:   GEN_DIR    := cores/$(TARGET)/generated\n67:   ORCH_TARGET_FLAG := --target $(TARGET)\n68:   # WORKTREE-mode paths (only consumed when WORKTREE= is set on `make loop`).\n69:   WT_BRANCH  := core-$(TARGET)\n70:   WT_PATH    := $(CURDIR)/.worktrees/$(TARGET)\n71: endif\n72: \n73: export RTL_DIR CORE_NAME OBJ_DIR GEN_DIR\n74: \n75: help:\n76: \t@echo \"Targets (most accept TARGET=<core_name>):\"\n77: \t@echo \"  make lint TARGET=v1     — verilator lint over cores/<TARGET>/rtl/*.sv\"\n78: \t@echo \"  make test TARGET=v1     — cocotb unit tests under cores/<TARGET>/test/\"\n79: \t@echo \"  make cosim TARGET=v1    — RVFI cosim against Python ISS\"\n80: \t@echo \"  make formal TARGET=v1   — riscv-formal fast suite (with ALTOPS)\"\n81: \t@echo \"  make formal-deep TARGET=v1 — full formal suite without ALTOPS (slow, bitvector-correct)\"\n82: \t@echo \"  make fpga TARGET=v1     — FPGA fitness eval (Fmax + CoreMark cycles)\"\n83: \t@echo \"  make bench              — build selftest + coremark ELFs\"\n84: \t@echo \"  make next TARGET=v1     — one orchestrator round\"\n85: \t@echo \"  make loop TARGET=v1 N=10 — N orchestrator rounds (auto-spawns .worktrees/<TARGET> on branch core-<TARGET>; pass WORKTREE= to opt out)\"\n86: \t@echo \"  make report TARGET=v1   — per-core experiment summary\"\n87: \t@echo \"  make clean TARGET=v1    — remove per-core build artifacts (use with TARGET=)\"\n88: \t@echo \"  make test-infra         — run orchestrator infra tests under tools/\"\n89: \t@echo \"\"\n90: \t@echo \"Available cores:\"\n91: \t@for d in cores/*/; do echo \"  - $$(basename $$d)\"; done 2>/dev/null || echo \"  (none yet)\"\n92: \n93: # verilator lint over $(RTL_DIR)/.\n94: # -Wno-MULTITOP: until phase 2's core.sv lands and instantiates everything,\n95: # rtl/ legitimately has multiple top modules. Drop this once phase 2 is in.\n96: lint:\n97: \t@if ls $(RTL_DIR)/*.sv >/dev/null 2>&1; then \\\n98: \t  verilator --lint-only -Wall -Wno-MULTITOP -sv +incdir+$(RTL_DIR) $(RTL_DIR)/*.sv; \\\n99: \telse \\\n100: \t  echo \"lint: no source files in $(RTL_DIR)/\"; \\\n101: \tfi\n102: \n103: test:\n104: \tpytest -v $(TEST_DIR)/\n105: \n106: test-infra:\n107: \tpytest -v tools/\n108: \n109: cosim: cosim-build bench/programs/selftest.elf bench/programs/coremark.elf\n110: \tpython3 -m tools.eval.cosim . $(TARGET)\n111: \n112: cosim-build: $(wildcard $(RTL_DIR)/*.sv) test/cosim/main.cpp\n113: \tbash test/cosim/build.sh\n114: \n115: bench/programs/selftest.elf: bench/programs/selftest.S bench/programs/link.ld\n116: \t$(MAKE) -f bench/programs/Makefile bench/programs/selftest.elf\n117: \n118: formal:\n119: \tbash formal/run_all.sh formal/checks.cfg\n120: \n121: # formal-deep: same checks WITHOUT RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS so bitwuzla\n122: # evaluates the actual MUL/DIV/REM bitvector formulas. SLOW (each\n123: # M-ext check can take 15+ min wall). Use periodically — the\n124: # orchestrator's per-iteration formal gate uses fast `make formal`.\n125: # See formal/checks.cfg comments for the full ALTOPS scope explanation.\n126: formal-deep:\n127: \tbash formal/run_all.sh formal/checks-deep.cfg\n128: \n129: bench:\n130: \t$(MAKE) -f bench/programs/Makefile all\n131: \n132: fpga: cosim-build bench/programs/coremark.elf $(GEN_DIR)/synth.json\n133: \tpython3 -m tools.eval.fpga . $(TARGET)\n134: \n135: bench/programs/coremark.elf: bench/programs/Makefile bench/programs/crt0.S \\\n136:                               $(wildcard bench/programs/coremark/*.c) \\\n137:                               $(wildcard bench/programs/coremark/*.h) \\\n138:                               $(wildcard bench/programs/coremark/baremetal/*.c) \\\n139:                               $(wildcard bench/programs/coremark/baremetal/*.h)\n140: \t$(MAKE) -f bench/programs/Makefile bench/programs/coremark.elf\n141: \n142: $(GEN_DIR)/synth.json: $(wildcard $(RTL_DIR)/*.sv) fpga/core_bench.sv fpga/scripts/synth.tcl\n143: \tmkdir -p $(GEN_DIR)\n144: \tyosys -c fpga/scripts/synth.tcl\n145: \n146: next:\n147: \tAGENT_PROVIDER=$(AGENT) python3 -m tools.orchestrator $(subst --iterations $(N),--iterations 1,$(ORCH_FLAGS)) $(ORCH_TARGET_FLAG)\n148: \n149: loop:\n150: ifneq ($(strip $(WORKTREE)),)\n151: \t@if [ ! -d \"$(WT_PATH)\" ]; then \\\n152: \t  echo \"[wt] creating branch $(WT_BRANCH) and worktree $(WT_PATH)\"; \\\n153: \t  if git rev-parse --verify $(WT_BRANCH) >/dev/null 2>&1; then \\\n154: \t    git worktree add \"$(WT_PATH)\" $(WT_BRANCH); \\\n155: \t  else \\\n156: \t    git worktree add -b $(WT_BRANCH) \"$(WT_PATH)\"; \\\n157: \t  fi; \\\n158: \t  [ -e \"$(WT_PATH)/formal/riscv-formal\" ] || ln -s \"$(CURDIR)/formal/riscv-formal\" \"$(WT_PATH)/formal/riscv-formal\"; \\\n159: \tfi\n160: \t@$(MAKE) -C \"$(WT_PATH)\" loop \\\n161: \t  WORKTREE= \\\n162: \t  TARGET=$(TARGET) N=$(N) K=$(K) AGENT=$(AGENT) \\\n163: \t  $(if $(strip $(BASE)),BASE=$(BASE),) \\\n164: \t  $(if $(strip $(COREMARK)),COREMARK=$(COREMARK),) \\\n165: \t  $(if $(strip $(LUT)),LUT=$(LUT),)\n166: else\n167: \tAGENT_PROVIDER=$(AGENT) python3 -m tools.orchestrator $(ORCH_FLAGS) $(ORCH_TARGET_FLAG)\n168: endif\n169: \n170: report:\n171: \tpython3 -m tools.orchestrator --report $(ORCH_TARGET_FLAG)\n172: \n173: clean:\n174: \trm -rf test/cosim/sim_build sim_build out\n175: \trm -rf experiments/worktrees\n176: \trm -f bench/programs/*.elf\n177: \trm -f test/*.result.xml\n178: \tfind test -name __pycache__ -prune -exec rm -rf {} + 2>/dev/null || true\n179: \tfind tools -name __pycache__ -prune -exec rm -rf {} + 2>/dev/null || true\n180: ifneq ($(strip $(TARGET)),)\n181: \trm -rf $(OBJ_DIR)\n182: \trm -rf $(GEN_DIR)\n183: \trm -rf cores/$(TARGET)/sim_build\n184: endif\n\n(End of file - total 184 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":".PHONY: help lint test test-infra cosim formal fpga next loop report bench clean\n.DEFAULT_GOAL := help\n\n# Resolve OSS CAD Suite path so commands work even when the user hasn't\n# sourced .toolchain/oss-cad-suite/environment in this shell.\nTOOLCHAIN_DIR := $(CURDIR)/.toolchain\nOSS_BIN       := $(TOOLCHAIN_DIR)/oss-cad-suite/bin\nLOCAL_BIN     := $(TOOLCHAIN_DIR)/bin\nexport PATH := $(OSS_BIN):$(LOCAL_BIN):$(PATH)\n\n# Orchestrator knobs (pass-through to tools.orchestrator):\n#   N        — number of rounds for `make loop` (default 10).\n#   K        — tournament size, slots per round (default 1 = sequential).\n#   AGENT    — codex (default) or claude. Honors a pre-existing\n#              AGENT_PROVIDER env var if AGENT isn't set on the make\n#              command line.\n#   BASE     — when forking a new TARGET, copy from cores/<BASE>/.\n#              Default: baseline (orchestrator-side default).\n#   COREMARK — target CoreMark iterations/sec (e.g. '370').\n#   LUT      — target LUT count (e.g. '3000').","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"Makefile","time":{"start":1777742692006,"end":1777742692013}},"id":"prt_de9b8b7010017qqjTNNxqfxErB","sessionID":"ses_2164e2417ffeuvidBdduDudYvn","messageID":"msg_de9b8a57e001CXaXwnTdOOZR31"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777742692978,"sessionID":"ses_2164e2417ffeuvidBdduDudYvn","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"glob","callID":"call_01_kIWpmmdZLzCF1gyIbikx8195","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"cores/bench/test/*.py"},"output":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs-pilot/deepseek-v4-pro-rep3/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260502-002-r1s1/cores/bench/test/test_reg_file.py\n/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs-pilot/deepseek-v4-pro-rep3/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260502-002-r1s1/cores/bench/test/test_pipeline.py\n/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs-pilot/deepseek-v4-pro-rep3/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260502-002-r1s1/cores/bench/test/test_imm_gen.py\n/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs-pilot/deepseek-v4-pro-rep3/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260502-002-r1s1/cores/bench/test/test_decoder.py\n/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs-pilot/deepseek-v4-pro-rep3/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260502-002-r1s1/cores/bench/test/conftest.py\n/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs-pilot/deepseek-v4-pro-rep3/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260502-002-r1s1/cores/bench/test/test_alu.py\n/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs-pilot/deepseek-v4-pro-rep3/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260502-002-r1s1/cores/bench/test/_helpers.py","metadata":{"count":7,"truncated":false},"title":"","time":{"start":1777742692965,"end":1777742692977}},"id":"prt_de9b8bfd9001coWPEAJdgIz9s9","sessionID":"ses_2164e2417ffeuvidBdduDudYvn","messageID":"msg_de9b8a57e001CXaXwnTdOOZR31"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777742695464,"sessionID":"ses_2164e2417ffeuvidBdduDudYvn","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_02_BYjMjGawKIxStwCiPs796695","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs-pilot/deepseek-v4-pro-rep3/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260502-002-r1s1/formal/run_all.sh"},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs-pilot/deepseek-v4-pro-rep3/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260502-002-r1s1/formal/run_all.sh</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: #!/usr/bin/env bash\n2: # Run riscv-formal checks against the current $RTL_DIR/*.sv.\n3: # Requires: formal/riscv-formal cloned (manual clone or `git submodule init`).\n4: #\n5: # Stages every $RTL_DIR/*.sv plus wrapper.sv + the chosen checks config under\n6: # the riscv-formal tree, then runs sby -> bitwuzla via the framework's\n7: # generated makefile. Tallies PASS/FAIL by inspecting each task's\n8: # logfile.txt.\n9: #\n10: # Usage: bash formal/run_all.sh [checks-cfg-path]\n11: #   default: formal/checks.cfg       (fast, ALTOPS, used by orchestrator)\n12: #   deep   : formal/checks-deep.cfg  (no ALTOPS, proves M-ext arithmetic)\n13: set -e\n14: \n15: if [ -z \"${RTL_DIR:-}\" ] || [ -z \"${CORE_NAME:-}\" ]; then\n16:   echo \"ERROR: formal/run_all.sh requires RTL_DIR and CORE_NAME env vars.\" >&2\n17:   echo \"  Example: RTL_DIR=cores/v1/rtl CORE_NAME=v1 bash formal/run_all.sh formal/checks.cfg\" >&2\n18:   exit 2\n19: fi\n20: \n21: SCRIPT_DIR=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"$0\")\" && pwd)\"\n22: PROJECT_ROOT=\"$(cd \"$SCRIPT_DIR/..\" && pwd)\"\n23: RISCV_FORMAL=\"$SCRIPT_DIR/riscv-formal\"\n24: CORE_DIR=\"$RISCV_FORMAL/cores/$CORE_NAME\"\n25: # Full output capture. Everything genchecks + make print lands here, so a\n26: # silent crash inside genchecks or a yosys error that doesn't match the\n27: # stdout grep filter is still recoverable post-mortem.\n28: LOG=\"$SCRIPT_DIR/last_run.log\"\n29: \n30: CHECKS_CFG=\"${1:-$SCRIPT_DIR/checks.cfg}\"\n31: if [ ! -f \"$CHECKS_CFG\" ]; then\n32:     echo \"ERROR: checks.cfg not found at $CHECKS_CFG\"\n33:     exit 1\n34: fi\n35: \n36: if [ ! -d \"$RISCV_FORMAL\" ]; then\n37:     echo \"ERROR: formal/riscv-formal not found. Clone it:\"\n38:     echo \"  git clone https://github.com/YosysHQ/riscv-formal $SCRIPT_DIR/riscv-formal\"\n39:     exit 1\n40: fi\n41: \n42: # OSS CAD Suite for consistent yosys / sby / bitwuzla. Homebrew yosys\n43: # combined with Homebrew bitwuzla has been observed to BrokenPipe inside\n44: # yosys-smtbmc.\n45: if [ -d \"$PROJECT_ROOT/.toolchain/oss-cad-suite/bin\" ]; then\n46:     export PATH=\"$PROJECT_ROOT/.toolchain/oss-cad-suite/bin:$PATH\"\n47: fi\n48: \n49: # Truncate the run log; genchecks + make are tee'd here in full.\n50: : > \"$LOG\"\n51: \n52: # Stage rtl + wrapper + the chosen checks config under the framework's\n53: # expected layout. genchecks.py looks for \"checks.cfg\" by name, so the\n54: # selected config is always copied to that filename in the core dir.\n55: mkdir -p \"$CORE_DIR\"\n56: # Clear stale .sv files first. Without this, a hypothesis that renames or\n57: # deletes a module in rtl/ leaves a ghost copy in $CORE_DIR from the\n58: # previous run, and genchecks/yosys silently picks up the old file\n59: # instead of the new one. CLAUDE.md explicitly grants hypotheses the\n60: # right to rename/delete files in rtl/, so this cleanup is required.\n61: rm -f \"$CORE_DIR\"/*.sv\n62: cp \"$PROJECT_ROOT/$RTL_DIR\"/*.sv \"$CORE_DIR/\"\n63: cp \"$SCRIPT_DIR/wrapper.sv\"     \"$CORE_DIR/wrapper.sv\"\n64: \n65: # Stage checks.cfg with [verilog-files] auto-derived from actual rtl/\n66: # contents instead of the cfg's hardcoded list. The shipped checks.cfg\n67: # enumerates the V0 baseline filenames; CLAUDE.md grants hypotheses the\n68: # right to add new modules, split a stage into multiple files, or rename\n69: # files in rtl/. Hardcoding silently fails on those restructurings (or\n70: # elaborates a stale ghost). Strip the original [verilog-files] section\n71: # and rebuild from the glob, with core_pkg.sv first and wrapper.sv last.\n72: STAGED_CFG=\"$CORE_DIR/checks.cfg\"\n73: awk '/^\\[verilog-files\\]/{exit} {print}' \"$CHECKS_CFG\" > \"$STAGED_CFG\"\n74: {\n75:     echo \"[verilog-files]\"\n76:     [ -f \"$CORE_DIR/core_pkg.sv\" ] && \\\n77:         echo \"@basedir@/cores/@core@/core_pkg.sv\"\n78:     for f in \"$CORE_DIR\"/*.sv; do\n79:         name=\"$(basename \"$f\")\"\n80:         [ \"$name\" = \"core_pkg.sv\" ] && continue\n81:         [ \"$name\" = \"wrapper.sv\" ] && continue\n82:         echo \"@basedir@/cores/@core@/$name\"\n83:     done\n84:     echo \"@basedir@/cores/@core@/wrapper.sv\"\n85: } >> \"$STAGED_CFG\"\n86: \n87: # genchecks.py expects @basedir@ = $RISCV_FORMAL, @core@ = $CORE_NAME.\n88: cd \"$CORE_DIR\"\n89: rm -rf checks/\n90: echo \"=== genchecks ===\" | tee -a \"$LOG\"\n91: python3 ../../checks/genchecks.py >> \"$LOG\" 2>&1\n92: cd checks\n93: \n94: JOBS=\"${JOBS:-$(sysctl -n hw.ncpu 2>/dev/null || nproc 2>/dev/null || echo 4)}\"\n95: echo \"=== make -j$JOBS -k ===\" | tee -a \"$LOG\"\n96: # Tee full output to LOG; show filtered progress on stdout. `-k` keeps\n97: # going past per-check errors so the .sby tally below sees every result\n98: # (NRET=2 means a few `_ch1` checks may PREUNSAT-error on single-issue\n99: # cores; without -k make stops on first error and 95+ checks never run,\n100: # producing a misleading failure list of unbuilt directories).\n101: make -j\"$JOBS\" -k -f makefile 2>&1 \\\n102:     | tee -a \"$LOG\" \\\n103:     | grep -E \"^(make|SBY|yosys|==|ERROR)\" || true\n104: \n105: shopt -s nullglob\n106: PASS=0; FAIL=0; FAILED=()\n107: for sby_file in *.sby; do\n108:     name=\"${sby_file%.sby}\"\n109:     log=\"$name/logfile.txt\"\n110:     if grep -q \"DONE (PASS\" \"$log\" 2>/dev/null; then\n111:         PASS=$((PASS+1))\n112:     elif [[ \"$name\" == *_ch1 ]] && grep -q \"Status: PREUNSAT\" \"$log\" 2>/dev/null; then\n113:         # Vacuous pass on channel-1 checks. NRET=2 contract: when a\n114:         # single-issue hypothesis ties io_rvfi_valid_1 to 0, the per-channel\n115:         # BMC's assumption (rvfi_valid_1=1) is unsatisfiable, and SBY\n116:         # reports Status: PREUNSAT (rc=16). The property holds vacuously\n117:         # over the empty set of ch1-valid traces — a legitimate pass.\n118:         # Dual-issue hypotheses make the assumption satisfiable, so this\n119:         # branch never matches and the regular DONE (PASS branch covers it.\n120:         PASS=$((PASS+1))\n121:     else\n122:         FAIL=$((FAIL+1)); FAILED+=(\"$name\")\n123:     fi\n124: done\n125: TOTAL=$((PASS+FAIL))\n126: if [ $TOTAL -eq 0 ]; then\n127:     FAIL=1\n128:     FAILED+=(\"no_checks_generated\")\n129: fi\n130: \n131: echo \"\"\n132: echo \"Formal: $PASS passed, $FAIL failed\"\n133: if [ $FAIL -gt 0 ]; then\n134:     echo \"Failed: ${FAILED[*]}\"\n135:     # Surface the FIRST failing check's logfile tail. tools/eval/formal.py\n136:     # captures this script's stdout/stderr into formal['detail'] and the\n137:     # orchestrator now records that in experiments/log.jsonl, so what we\n138:     # print here is what shows up as the diagnostic for the failed run.\n139:     first=\"${FAILED[0]}\"\n140:     if [ -f \"$first/logfile.txt\" ]; then\n141:         echo \"\"\n142:         echo \"--- $first/logfile.txt (last 30 lines) ---\"\n143:         tail -30 \"$first/logfile.txt\"\n144:     fi\n145:     echo \"\"\n146:     echo \"Full run log: $LOG\"\n147:     echo \"Per-check logs in: $CORE_DIR/checks/<check>/logfile.txt\"\n148: fi\n149: [ $FAIL -eq 0 ]\n\n(End of file - total 149 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# Run riscv-formal checks against the current $RTL_DIR/*.sv.\n# Requires: formal/riscv-formal cloned (manual clone or `git submodule init`).\n#\n# Stages every $RTL_DIR/*.sv plus wrapper.sv + the chosen checks config under\n# the riscv-formal tree, then runs sby -> bitwuzla via the framework's\n# generated makefile. Tallies PASS/FAIL by inspecting each task's\n# logfile.txt.\n#\n# Usage: bash formal/run_all.sh [checks-cfg-path]\n#   default: formal/checks.cfg       (fast, ALTOPS, used by orchestrator)\n#   deep   : formal/checks-deep.cfg  (no ALTOPS, proves M-ext arithmetic)\nset -e\n\nif [ -z \"${RTL_DIR:-}\" ] || [ -z \"${CORE_NAME:-}\" ]; then\n  echo \"ERROR: formal/run_all.sh requires RTL_DIR and CORE_NAME env vars.\" >&2\n  echo \"  Example: RTL_DIR=cores/v1/rtl CORE_NAME=v1 bash formal/run_all.sh formal/checks.cfg\" >&2\n  exit 2\nfi\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"formal/run_all.sh","time":{"start":1777742695459,"end":1777742695463}},"id":"prt_de9b8c3b4001Yy8Cv9Vyz2sYT2","sessionID":"ses_2164e2417ffeuvidBdduDudYvn","messageID":"msg_de9b8a57e001CXaXwnTdOOZR31"}}
